reviews_data.review_text: Never had a problem before but my visit 11/21 morning was terrible. Order 2 milk teas and it was watered down. I order less ice and the drink was crazy. Obviously the guy didn't know what he was doing there was no "milk or tea" literally bland no flavor in both. Wont be back at this location.

The classic black milk tea is pretty good. It's not too sweet and not too milky. And they use a milk powder so it's not harsh on the stomach for those who are lactose intolerant. You can actually taste the black tea

I’ve been a loyal Kung Fu Tea customer since before the South Blvd location even opened, but I’ve consistently experienced issues with this store’s hours and product availability. The app should not allow customers to place orders or pay (including tips) for items that are out of stock or when the store is closed.

This isn’t a one-off occasion — it’s unfortunately become the norm for this location. There have been multiple times—at least five—when I placed and paid for an order only to find the location closed or missing key ingredients like milk cap or boba. I truly love my usual order, but after today’s experience, I can no longer justify spending my money here.
nice place to get quick cool tea!
I always stop here after a hard days work and it never ceases to lift my spirits. Love it.

Kung fu tea is the best bubble tea franchise in America. They have all different types, from milk, to fruit, to basically icees (or slurpees). They also have about 15 different kinds of "toppings", from tapioca to aloe, to jelly, to popping bubbles. Some also have food. I recommend it

Shakira... was who waited on us? And she was very helpful with everything she helped us with our boba teas, a very nice girl, showed us a lot of little places in the city that were good to visit while we were in town. Thanks again for your recommendations. We did everything you said and it was cool. This place is good for boba tea lots of selection, very good location next door as well
Their brown sugar boba is my favorite. Also, black tea connoisseurs try the honey oolong milk tea!
Love Kung Fu Tea! The south blvd location has always gotten my drink orders right, super attentive and quick even when there’s only one person working.

This location is always slow and never has anything in stock. We shouldn’t have to wait over 10-15 minutes in line and then another 15-20 minutes for drinks. They’re always out of something. How can you be out of boba in the middle of the day? Or out of both milk caps? It’s giving that y’all just don’t want to make them. If that’s the case, please condense your menu and stop offering things. At this point, I’ll just have to drive to the other location in Charlotte.
very friendly and patient. place had a nice design and looked clean. thank you!
My girls wanted boba tea and they said they were really delicious. Excellent service. Nice atmosphere with good ambiance and clean restrooms.
Highly recommended place great vibe feels comfy inside and quiet and clean. Owner is so kind and friendly. Best of all iv loved my drink!! Thank you honored you 5 stars!

This place is soo cute. They have different types of teas, slushes, lemonades and more. I ordered the tropical punch which is like a lemonade. It only came in a large for $6 which wasn’t bad. It was soooo good. Definitely can’t wait to go back and try more stuff.
Except for the fact that the number of flavors are overwhelming for a first timer, everything is pretty perfect at this place. Register staff are helpful. Drinks are yummy!

disappointing experience here. they did not have anything ready or available, they were out of teas, most boba drinks. not sure why they weren’t prepared before opening.

-3/8 12pm: went in to get the boba that the manager offered, again the place did not have any boba available. i just can’t imagine why a boba place would not have products available especially on a saturday when they would get a lot of business. its just unfortunate.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello Izzy,

We had a staffing issue where someone had called out last minute. We apologize for the inconvenience.  For you next visit we will get a you a free drinks and toppings on the house. Just let us know when you'd like to come redeem this.

Thank you!

reviews_data.review_text: Best boba! Love that they have so many flavors!

We were excited to try this place but unfortunately it was not very accommodating to those with a vegan diet or if you are lactose intolerant. Oddly other bubble tea places use non dairy powder in bubble teas and we haven’t had issues but here you can only pick the items listed under “Milk Strike” to sub in oat milk and they would not make any menu modifications when asked to add oat milk in something else. Hopefully this review helps our fellow vegans!

reviews_data.review_text: This was my first time ever having boba, and the employees were nothing but helpful when I asked so many questions. They were super patient and just overall amazing. I a mango slush with mango jelly and it was AMAZING, Definitely coming again

I got a honey oolong tea and a piece of plastic netting came up through the straw. I immediately went back to the store and they had just closed. They were still behind the counter and met eyes with me but yet refused to acknowledge my presence or even my complaint after I called
to let them know why I was standing outside. Being ignored was demoralizing and unprofessional and she didn’t even apologize or offer a refund. I threw my drink away because it was disgusting to sip that through a straw, totally threw me off.

Thank you,

KFT Management

Hello Chelsea!

The pineapple white grape lemonade was soo good, omg. Just the right amount of sweetness, had pineapple pulp in the bottom and was really refreshing. I wish I would have ordered another one since i live out of town. Other than the temperature in the building, everything was great!!!

I came here because of the T-Mobile Tuesday reward they offered from last week $2 off and I had to try it for a number of reasons of course because of the great reviews, I love boba tea and it’s right down the street from my job. I sat up an account to use the discount and to start earning points. The decor was very cute on the inside and the staff was very nice, explaining how to use the app and all of their drinks. I went with the winter melon tea 50% sweet and regular ice (I should’ve went lite on the ice you get more tea) with popping mango and my husband got oolong hot tea 20% sweet. I was very impressed with the taste of both of them not like most teas you get it had a freshness to them. I will get one of slushes next time that’s what everyone else got. I’ll be back soon.
Classic milk tea. Ask for 75% sweetness will probably be perfect for me. Need large size for next time.

Friendly staff. Fast service. Plenty of customizable options. App rewards. A nice treat myself reward for longer days. Right amount of caffeine/sugar pick-me-up.

Parking in the plaza can be rough during peak times, so if you have the app, order ahead to get in and out without having to circle around for a space.

Very close to the Scaleybark train stop. If you time it correctly and keep a good pace, you can order on the app at the train station, walk to this location and walk back in time for the next train.

My favorite Kung Fu Tea location because of the amazing staff. My drink is always spot on and building is always clean. Thank you for a great experience every time!
Kind people, and great drinks!

My (now) husband and I are obsessed with boba and it just made sense to have some on our wedding day with our entire wedding party! Hoang, the manager of this location, was so wonderful to work with, and Hoang made sure we were well taken care of. We gifted our wedding party bobamates to use for our post-ceremony photos and asked KFT if we could have our boba in the bottles. They worked with us to make sure it could happen, and we couldn’t have had a better experience! Hoang was so responsive and accommodating, and the boba tasted amazing, as usual with KFT. KFT is our favorite boba go-to so when we were able to drink it between the ceremony and reception, it was seriously such a treat to keep us going throughout the day. We were able to delegate drop off and pick up easily because we trusted this location to take care of us, and happy to say that there were no issues. All we needed to do was sign a waiver (for having our drinks in the bobamates), order & pay through the mobile app, and drop off the bottles. I was even able to order a couple extra on the side for my niece and friends picking up without any confusion. Now, we can look back at these photos and remember what an easy and great time it was! Thank you so much Hoang and the rest of the staff who made this happen for us.
Boba 10/10, tea 5/10. Maybe I’m just not a fan of the milk powder used in their milk teas. The places I typically go to do not use this. Good service though 👍🏻

I always enjoy my Kung Fu Tea, but this time I was disappointed. I ordered Oreo Wow, but there was no oreo at all. I was the only customer in the store at the moment, so I didn't expect the staff to be careless.
P/S: There was also a kung fu milk tea in the order, and the taste was bland even though I ordered no ice but regular sugar. It tasted like there's more tea than milk than usual.
Riquisimo

Didn't like their tea very much. Won't be back. They also had Thai tea that wasn't orange which was weird.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello Neosovereign,

I'm sorry you didn't find our drink to be to your tastes. First I would like to explain that with our Thai Tea formula, we have taken out the artificial coloring from the tea, that will leave it to appear in a light caramel color instead of the traditional orange.

As a gesture of our dedication to give us another try, we will offer you one large drink with topping(s) of your choice on the house for your next visit.

If you wish to redeem this, please message or email us at adassi.jess@gmail.com and we will be sure to notify the store prior to your visit.

Thank you for giving us a try, and we hope to see you again to grab your free drink. We really appreciate your feedback, as it helps us understand the tastes of our patrons and thus make better suggestions.

Sincerely,

Hoang Nguyen

reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello Ramya,

We are sad to hear that our products weren’t up to our regular standards which resulted in your bad experience with our location.

For this could be many different reasons, we do recommend that iced drinks with tapioca pearls be consumed within the first 2 hours of  the drink being made due to its nature of getting chewier and harder as it stays in colder temperature. As for the taro milk tea, the mango popping bubbles we have in house can definitely have that fruity, sweet and sour taste to it. We definitely recommend you trying the creamy taro milk tea with our other variety of more fitting toppings like Oreos, Herbal Jelly, Milk cap, etc.

As a gesture of our dedication to give us another try, we will offer you one large drink with topping(s) of your choice on the house for your next visit.

If you wish to redeem this, please message or email us at adassi.jess@gmail.com and we will be sure to notify the store prior to your visit.

Thank you for giving us a try, and we hope to see you again to grab your free drink. We really appreciate your feedback, as it helps us understand the tastes of our patrons and thus make better suggestions.

Sincerely,

Hoang Nguyen

What a disappointment for us today! We’re a regular customer at Kungfu Tea up North so we’re excited to find Kungfu Tea here in Charlotte. We ordered our usual drink of Thai milk tea, Kungfu milk tea and brown sugar milk tea and we couldn’t tell much different of each drink because we tasted milk but no other flavor. My kids even said it tasted like the milk in their cereal. I gave two stars because the girl at the cashier was nice.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello Cac Mai!

First of all, I appreciate you being a loyal fan of Kung Fu Tea and thus visiting us. I'm sorry you didn't receive a product you expected. I assure you, that we follow all the same procedures and recipes for all other kung fu teas around the nation. If this wasn't to your liking, we would love for you to come back and redeem any two drinks for free of equal value.

We also appreciate that you recognize that our service is at least satisfactory. If you were to come back and receive your free drinks, please be sure to send us a reply here and we will notify the store to be ready for your arrival. And while there, we would love to hear more of what you thought about your experience so that we we can be further aware of our quality.

We really appreciate your comments and feedback, as this helps us improve our practices.

Hope to hear from you soon.

Cheers,

Vinh Le
Owner

Awesome bubble tea. Been our regular place

Definitely was disappointed. Order large Taro drink with 0% sugar, no milk sub almond and they did opposite. Call back and found out they never had almond milk. Drink was over sweet. Please save your money and go to Tea Fusion(restaurant near university blvd).
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello Shay,

I apologize for your experience at our store. At Kung Fu tea, there aren't any milk substitutes. It may be confusing as there is an Almond Milk tea. But that is an Almond flavored milk tea. Also, as a quick note, about 95% of our offerings are Lactose free, including our milk teas (Thai tea is the only one with lactose). It is true that our drinks do come rather sweet, which is the reason why we suggest to reduce it depending on the drink.

Taro is one of the sweeter drinks, which you rightfully reduced it to 0%. Since this was too sweet, might I suggest trying another Milk tea that has only one type of sweetener (regular milk tea, Honey, Coconut, or coffee).

As a way to make up for your experience, I invite you to come back and grab one FREE MEDIUM DRINK WITH ONE TOPPING of your choosing. To redeem this, please message us back via e-mail (kungfuteaclt@gmail.com) and let us know when you plan on coming if you choose to do so.

Thank you for coming to Kung Fu Tea and also giving us feedback. We appreciate your comments as it helps us serve all of you better.

Sincerely,

Vinh Le

reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello Shay,

I apologize for your experience at our store. At Kung Fu tea, there aren't any milk substitutes. It may be confusing as there is an Almond Milk tea. But that is an Almond flavored milk tea. Also, as a quick note, about 95% of our offerings are Lactose free, including our milk teas (Thai tea is the only one with lactose). It is true that our drinks do come rather sweet, which is the reason why we suggest to reduce it depending on the drink.

Taro is one of the sweeter drinks, which you rightfully reduced it to 0%. Since this was too sweet, might I suggest trying another Milk tea that has only one type of sweetener (regular milk tea, Honey, Coconut, or coffee).

As a way to make up for your experience, I invite you to come back and grab one FREE MEDIUM DRINK WITH ONE TOPPING of your choosing. To redeem this, please message us back via e-mail (kungfuteaclt@gmail.com) and let us know when you plan on coming if you choose to do so.

Thank you for coming to Kung Fu Tea and also giving us feedback. We appreciate your comments as it helps us serve all of you better.

Sincerely,

Vinh Le
